# Reflection – Assignment 8

One of the main challenges in this assignment was deciding the level of detail to include in state and activity diagrams. Including too many states made diagrams complex, while too few reduced clarity.

Another challenge was aligning diagrams with previously defined user stories and functional requirements. Ensuring consistency required revisiting earlier assignments.

State diagrams focus on object behavior over time, while activity diagrams focus on workflow processes. Understanding this difference was important in creating accurate diagrams.

Additionally, representing parallel processes in activity diagrams required careful design to ensure correctness.

Overall, this assignment improved understanding of system behavior and how different UML diagrams complement each other in system design.
